It works from JS, and python errors also show up. But my Django/python logging calls don't show up. However, everything works fine when running in production (on Heroku).

For example...
```
logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)
def some_method():
    logger.info('this does not show up in Rollbar when running locally')
```

My local environment is virtually the same as prod with the usual differences... DEBUG = True, etc.

Here are my relevant settings...
```
ENVIRONMENT = 'development'
ROLLBAR = {
 'access_token': 'xxxxxxxx',
'branch': 'master',
'root': os.getcwd(),
'environment': ENVIRONMENT,
}
LOGGING = {
 'version': 1,
'disable_existing_loggers': False,
'filters': {
 'require_debug_false': {
 '()': 'django.utils.log.RequireDebugFalse',
}
 },
'handlers': {
 'console': {
 'level': 'INFO',
'class': 'logging.StreamHandler',
},
'rollbar': {
 'filters': ['require_debug_false'],
'access_token': ROLLBAR['access_token'],
'class': 'rollbar.logger.RollbarHandler',
'environment': ENVIRONMENT,
},
},
'loggers': {
 'celery': {
 'handlers': ['console', 'rollbar'],
'level': 'INFO',
'propagate': True,
},
'': {
 'handlers': ['console', 'rollbar'],
'level': 'INFO',
'propagate': True,
},
},
}
```

They're not showing up in the frames at all with this config:

ROLLBAR = {
    'access_token': ROLLBAR_ACCESS_TOKEN,
    'environment': CURRENT_ENVIRONMENT,
    'root': ROOT_DIR,
    'enabled': True if ROLLBAR_ACCESS_TOKEN else False,
    'locals': {
        'enabled': True,
        'safe_repr': False,
    }
}

pyrollbar 0.13.16

